- The file malloc.txt is a text file having the user-documentation for the
	malloc subsystem
- The file Files contains a list of each of the file and what it does
- typing 'make' should be enough to build libmalloc.a
- typing 'make test' should build the malloc_t test program
- debugging programs using libmalloc relies on the setting of the MALLOC_DEBUG
	environmental variable (see malloc.txt for more information.
- output from programs using libmalloc goes to the filename stored in the
	MALLOC_LOGFILE environmental variable (setenv MALLOC_LOGFILE filename).
